videos.headline: Mann drives and floats one up
videos.description: Florida State's Terrance Mann fakes the three, drives, flies and lays it in for the nice finish.

videos.headline: Koumadje gets air and crushes the rim
videos.description: Off the inbounds pass, Florida State's Trent Forrest floats it up and Christ Koumadje throws it down.

videos.headline: FSU's D leads to Gray dunk
videos.description: UAB's Jalen Perry misses a 3-pointer to give Florida State the easy fast break and a Raiquan Gray dunk.

videos.headline: Scott-Grayson drives, scoops and scores
videos.description: UAB's Tyreek Scott-Grayson drives from the wing, pauses, finds the hole and finishes at the rim.

videos.headline: Bryant gets steal then finishes strong at the rim
videos.description: UAB's Zack Bryant collects the steal, drives, takes on the Florida State defense extends and finishes at the rim.

videos.headline: Mann throws down two-handed flush
videos.description: Florida State's Terrance Mann hesitates on the right wing, then blows by the defender for a nasty two-handed dunk.

article.linkText: No. 14 Florida St to face No. 19 LSU at AdvoCare
article.story: LAKE BUENA VISTA, Fla. -- Terance Mann scored 17 points and No. 14 Florida State advanced to the AdvoCare Invitational semifinals with an 81-63 victory over UAB on Thursday night. The unbeaten Seminoles (4-0) will play No. 19 LSU on Friday night for a spot in Sunday's championship game. The Tigers defeated College of Charleston 67-55. Defending national champion Villanova and Oklahoma State square off in the other semifinal. Christ Koumadje had 12 points and nine rebounds for Florida State. Mfiondu Kabengele, the nephew of former NBA All-Star center Dikembe Mutombo, added 10 points. Tyreek Scott-Grayson scored 16 for UAB (3-1). The Blazers, who trailed 44-37 with 17 minutes remaining, will face College of Charleston in the consolation bracket Friday.
